==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|abstemius|abstēmius|abstaining from wine|lang=la}}; from {{term|ab|lang=la}}, {{term|abs|lang=la}} + root of {{term|temetum|tēmētum|[[intoxicating]] drink|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/æbˈstɛmi.əs/}}
* {{rhymes|iːmiəs}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{context|Original Latin sense}} [[abstaining|Abstaining]] from wine.
#: Under his special eye '''Abstemious''' I grew up and thrived amain. - [[w:John Milton|John Milton]]
# [[sparing|Sparing]] in diet; [[refraining]] from a free use of food and strong drinks; [[temperate]]; [[abstinent]]; [[sparing]] in the [[indulgence]] of the appetite or passions.
#: Instances of longevity are chiefly among the '''abstemious''' - [[w:John Arbuthnot|John Arbuthnot]].
# [[sparing|Sparingly]] used; used with [[temperance]] or [[moderation]]
#: an '''abstemious''' diet - [[w:Edward Gibbon|Edward Gibbon]]
# Marked by, or [[spent]] in, [[abstinence]]; as, an ''abstemious'' life.
#: One '''abstemious''' day. - [[w:Alexander Pope|Alexander Pope]]
# {{rare}} [[promotive|Promotive]] of [[abstemiousness]]
#: Such is the virtue of the '''abstemious''' well. - [[w:John Dryden|John Dryden]]
